{
  "texts": [
    "Poetry example Suppose we are interested in the anthropomorphism of birds in Emily Dickinson's poems.",
    "The input texts T are the poems, and the target entities X are words referring to birds like \"bird,\" \"hummingbird\", \"owl\", etc.",
    "Then, our method outputs ANTHROSCORE for each poem as well as each sentence mentioning a bird.",
    "For calculating P HUM and P OBJ, we use the following lists of pronouns: set.",
    "In each round, for each sentence, the annotators indicated whether the sentence implies that the masked term is capable of affective mental states, behavioral potential, or cognitive mental states (Def. 1)."
  ]
}